{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_oZRyJ9ObCcfETPlYucGO8o3H","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_tables\n3\toutput:\n4\t  tables: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, read_sources, user_stories]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tDetail EVERY table `plan_app` planned into a source-grounded data model — one entry per\n11\t`plan_app.tables`, same set, no additions and no drops (membership was decided upstream where the whole\n12\tapp was in view). `query`, `read_sources` (`read_sources.summary`, the build brief), `user_stories`\n13\t(`user_stories.stories` — the jobs each table must support), and `plan_app` (`plan_app.tables`, the\n14\tBINDING list) are in scope. This is still a THINKING step — no writers.\n15\t\n16\tFor every planned table produce its full `schema` AND the actual `rows` read from the material, so the\n17\timplement step seeds data at creation. Do NOT invent rows: use only values the source states\n18\t(identifiers, contacts, dates, payments, stated totals, attribution). Mine the brief HARD for each\n19\ttable's rows before concluding it has few — the acceptance checks in `user_stories` name the specific\n20\tdata that must land. If after a genuine search a planned table truly has no rows in the material, keep\n21\tit with an empty `rows: []` and a complete schema rather than dropping it — the plan is binding — but\n22\tthat should be rare; a planned table almost always has rows if you look.\n23\t\n24\tEvery table schema needs a `title`, a `description`, and `columns` where each column has a\n25\t`description` and exactly one uuid primary key. Keys in each row object MUST match the column names.\n26\tEmit one statement:\n27\t\n28\t```typescript\n29\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n30\t  tables: [\n31\t    {\n32\t      name: '<source-derived table name>',\n33\t      schema: {\n34\t        title: '<Title>',\n35\t        description: '<what this table stores>',\n36\t        columns: {\n37\t          id: { type: 'string', description: 'Primary key', primaryKey: true, generated: 'uuid' },\n38\t          // …one column per field the record carries, each with a real description.\n39\t        },\n40\t      },\n41\t      // One object per record READ FROM THE MATERIAL. Never carry over an example value.\n42\t      rows: [ /* { id: '…', …source-derived fields } */ ],\n43\t    },\n44\t  ],\n45\t});\n46\t```\n47\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_sc8TxR4N98D3JKwXfOKvuRrQ","session_id":"10d74089-d65b-435d-a979-1d29f6775b52","uuid":"2b9c373f-c462-4535-b1af-042d6b4988a1","timestamp":"2026-07-16T22:24:43.635Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace appbuilder timeout"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_RE7sVYSZFzjS0C1SW4P7VNAP","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: plan_pages\n3\toutput:\n4\t  pages: array\n5\tdependsOn: [plan_app, plan_endpoints, plan_components, user_stories]\n6\trole: general\n7\tfunctions: []\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\tDetail the MULTIPLE pages of the app, each wired to the real endpoints and the reusable components, so\n11\tthat every user story has a page that satisfies it. `query`, `user_stories` (`user_stories.stories` —\n12\teach page must serve one or more), `plan_app` (`plan_app.pages`, the binding page list), `plan_endpoints`\n13\t(`plan_endpoints.endpoints` — each is `{ name, route, purpose, tables }`), and `plan_components`\n14\t(`plan_components.components`) are in scope. This is a THINKING step — no writers. **Every endpoint a\n15\tpage lists must be an existing `plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name`, copied VERBATIM — never invent a name\n16\tor transform one.** Detail the `index` home PLUS the additional views the stories call for (a list, a\n17\tdetail `items/[id]`, a dashboard) — a single page is not enough. For each page, list the endpoint\n18\t`name`s it reads and the components it renders, so the implement step wires real data through shared UI.\n19\tEmit one statement:\n20\t\n21\t```typescript\n22\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n23\t  pages: [\n24\t    {\n25\t      route: 'index',\n26\t      purpose: '<what this page shows>',\n27\t      // endpoint NAMES, each copied verbatim from plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name:\n28\t      endpoints: [ '<endpoint name>' ],\n29\t      // component names (from plan_components) this page renders:\n30\t      components: [ '<ComponentName>' ],\n31\t    },\n32\t  ],\n33\t});\n34\t```\n35\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_sc8TxR4N98D3JKwXfOKvuRrQ","session_id":"10d74089-d65b-435d-a979-1d29f6775b52","uuid":"9ae85061-6a4b-4b6a-a2c4-f9fbfe32bc59","timestamp":"2026-07-16T22:24:43.637Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace appbui