{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_Ll4HUDgUSI2oEBwQxQccxecD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: implement_pages\n3\toutput:\n4\t  route: string\n5\t  ok: boolean\n6\tdependsOn: [plan_pages, plan_endpoints, plan_components, implement_components]\n7\tforEach: plan_pages.pages\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite ONE React page into the LIVE project's `pages/`. Your page is in `item` =\n13\t{ route, purpose, endpoints, components } (`index` is the home; `items/[id]` is a dynamic route).\n14\t`plan_endpoints.endpoints` and `plan_components.components` are in scope. Write the FULL `.tsx` source\n15\tinline with the array-`join(\"\\n\")` pattern (real line breaks).\n16\t\n17\tWiring rules — the app fails to compile if you break them:\n18\t- Import data hooks ONLY from `@app/runtime` (`useApi`/`useApiMutation`/`apiCall`/`Link`/`useParams`) —\n19\t  never `fetch` a raw URL, and NEVER import `react-router`, `@radix-ui/*`, `@agent-chat/react`, or a\n20\t  relative `use-api`; none exist in a generated project.\n21\t- Read data by passing an endpoint `name` to `useApi` — the exact stable id the endpoint exported. Use\n22\t  ONLY names listed for this page in `item.endpoints` (each is a real `plan_endpoints.endpoints[].name`);\n23\t  never invent or transform a name. Every read endpoint returns `{ items: [...] }`, so read `data.items`.\n24\t- IMPORT the reusable components you planned, by relative path from `pages/` to `components/`: a\n25\t  top-level page uses `../components/<Name>`, a page one directory deep uses `../../components/<Name>`.\n26\t- STYLE WITH `@lmthing/css` DESIGN TOKENS ONLY (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted`,\n27\t  `border-border`) — never a raw hex, `rgb()/hsl()`, or a stock Tailwind color.\n28\t\n29\t`writeProjectPage` validates the page has a default export and parses, returning `{ ok, error? }`;\n30\trewrite and retry if `w.ok` is false. Emit one statement:\n31\t\n32\t```typescript\n33\tconst pg = item;\n34\tconst depth = String(pg.route).split('/').length; // 'index' → 1, 'items/[id]' → 2\n35\tconst up = '../'.repeat(depth);                    // '../' to reach the project root from this page\n36\tconst ep = (Array.isArray(pg.endpoints) && pg.endpoints[0]) ? pg.endpoints[0]\n37\t  : (plan_endpoints.endpoints[0] ? plan_endpoints.endpoints[0].name : 'items-list');\n38\tconst comp = (Array.isArray(pg.components) && pg.components[0]) ? pg.components[0]\n39\t  : (plan_components.components[0] ? plan_components.components[0].name : null);\n40\tconst src = [\n41\t  \"import { useApi } from '@app/runtime';\",\n42\t  comp ? (\"import \" + comp + \" from '\" + up + \"components/\" + comp + \"';\") : \"\",\n43\t  \"\",\n44\t  \"export default function Page() {\",\n45\t  \"  const { data, isLoading, error } = useApi<{ items: { id: string; title?: string }[] }>('\" + ep + \"');\",\n46\t  \"  if (isLoading) return <p className=\\\"p-4 text-muted\\\">Loading…</p>;\",\n47\t  \"  if (error) return <p className=\\\"p-4 text-destructive\\\">Could not load data.</p>;\",\n48\t  \"  return (\",\n49\t  \"    <main className=\\\"space-y-2 p-4\\\">\",\n50\t  \"      {(data?.items ?? []).map((it) => (\",\n51\t  comp ? (\"        <\" + comp + \" key={it.id} title={it.title ?? it.id} />\") : \"        <div key={it.id} className=\\\"text-foreground\\\">{it.title ?? it.id}</div>\",\n52\t  \"      ))}\",\n53\t  \"    </main>\",\n54\t  \"  );\",\n55\t  \"}\",\n56\t].filter((line) => line !== \"\").join(\"\\n\");\n57\tconst w = writeProjectPage(pg.route, src);\n58\tcurrentTask.resolve({ route: pg.route, ok: w.ok });\n59\t```\n60\t\n61\tThe page TSX is typechecked against a **NO-DOM ambient** (no `console`/`window`). Data comes only from\n62\t`useApi(<endpoint name>)`; the endpoint name is one of `item.endpoints`, copied VERBATIM.\n63\t\n64\t✅ **The page source should look like this** (hooks from `@app/runtime`, verbatim endpoint name, component\n65\tby relative path, tokens, reads `data.items`):\n66\t\n67\t```tsx\n68\timport { useApi } from '@app/runtime';\n69\timport CostCard from '../components/CostCard';\n70\t\n71\texport default function Page() {\n72\t  const { data, isLoading, error } = useApi<{ items: { id: string; title?: string }[] }>('cost-lines');\n73\t  if (isLoading) return <p className=\"p-4 text-muted\">Loading…</p>;\n74\t  if (error) return <p className=\"p-4 text-destructive\">Could not load data.</p>;\n75\t  return (\n76\t    <main className=\"space-y-2 p-4\">\n77\t      {(data?.items ?? []).map((it) => <CostCard key={it.id} title={it.title ?? it.id} />)}\n78\t    </main>\n79\t  );\n80\t}\n81\t```\n82\t\n83\t❌ **Never emit any of these** — each one fails the compile or breaks the wiring:\n84\t\n85\t```tsx\n86\timport { useRoute } from 'react-router';          // ✗ react-router is not in a generated project\n87\timport * as Dialog from '@radix-ui/react-dialog'; // ✗ no @radix-ui\n88\timport { useApi } from '../use-api';              // ✗ hooks come ONLY from '@app/runtime'\n89\tuseApi('costLines');                              // ✗ invented / transformed name — use item.endpoints verbatim\n90\tconst res = await fetch('/api/cost-lines');       // ✗ no raw fetch — read through useApi\n91\t<div className=\"text-blue-600\">                   // ✗ stock Tailwind color — use text-foreground\n92\tconsole.log(data);                                // ✗ Cannot find name 'console' — no DOM lib\n93\t```\n94\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_sc8TxR4N98D3JKwXfOKvuRrQ","session_id":"10d74089-d65b-435d-a979-1d29f6775b52","uuid":"71f01705-87ed-42ce-ac50-a492fcdc17bb","timestamp":"2026-07-16T22:24:45.268Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace appbuilder timeout"}
