{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a976be3c633651073","tool_use_id":"call_sc8TxR4N98D3JKwXfOKvuRrQ","status":"completed","output_file":"/tmp/claude-1000/-home-vasilis-LMTHING-lmthing/10d74089-d65b-435d-a979-1d29f6775b52/tasks/a976be3c633651073.output","summary":"## Finding\n\nThis was **not an app-authoring failure**. The automator completed the full live-project pipeline; the observed `appManifest.built: false` is a **snapshot/build-status timing artifact**, while the harness marked the overall turn interrupted just before its 20-minute cap.\n\n### Trace evidence\n\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/2/06-tanzania/step-02.full.json`\n  - Records the outer turn as `durationMs: 910351`, `interrupted: true`, before the harness’s normal 1,200,000 ms cap.\n  - State already has six populated tables and page routes, but snapshot sets `\"built\": false`.\n  - The tasklist’s source trace is:\n    `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/sessions/6d75160f-373d-4904-bfe8-38b990da1f8c/trace.json`\n    - `tasklist:build_live_project` completed in **671,325 ms**.\n    - `delegate:system-appbuilder/automator/build_live_project` completed in **683,686 ms**.\n    - It wrote **9 normal pages plus `_layout`** and completed `finalize`.\n    - Tasklist model work: **53 LLM responses**, about **286,606 input** and **38,667 output tokens**.\n    - The parent `organize_material` tasklist took **923,980 ms** because it also built the three specialist spaces. The overall session then ended error/interrupted around **943,507 ms**.\n\n- The same round’s step 3 proves the authored app was buildable:\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/2/06-tanzania/step-03.full.json`\n  - `POST /app/build` reports `built: true`, six routes, and root page HTTP 200.\n  - Therefore `built:false` at step 2 does not mean the automator omitted pages or produced an invalid app.\n\n- The generated project currently contains all necessary artifacts:\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/database/`\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/api/`\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/components/`\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/pages/`\n  - It also now has `.data/pages-dist/index.html` and `.data/pages-cache.json`.\n\n## Where time goes\n\nThe expensive portion is structurally expected model work, not the writers:\n\n| Phase | Trace duration | Notes |\n|---|---:|---|\n| `read_sources` | 97.6 s | 15 model responses, plus two recoverable nullability typecheck retries |\n| `plan_tables` | 263.2 s | Dominant appbuilder node; source-derived schemas and all rows for six tables |\n| `implement_tables` | 9.1 s aggregate wall completion | Six concurrent per-table writers |\n| `plan_endpoints` | 25.3 s | One recoverable `console.warn` typecheck retry |\n| `implement_endpoints` | 58.9 s aggregate wall completion | 13 per-endpoint model writers |\n| `plan_components` | 58.9 s | Runs once endpoints are available |\n| `implement_components` | 78.6 s aggregate wall completion | Six writers |\n| `plan_pages` | 78.6 s | Depends on component plan/endpoints |\n| `implement_pages` | 64.1 s aggregate wall completion | Nine page writers |\n| `finalize` | 4.7 s | Writes `_layout`/Chat dock and resolves |\n\nThe outer tasklist is serial at phase boundaries (`read → stories → app plan → tables → endpoints → components → pages → finalize`) and the shared `ForkEngine` caps each fan-out to **four concurrent forks**. The Tanzania request induced six tables, 13 endpoints, six components, and nine content pages, so the pipeline necessarily queues multiple batches.\n\nRelevant structure:\n\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/index.md`\n  - Explicitly specifies a complete, per-item plan/build pipeline.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/04-plan_tables.md`\n  - Requires every table schema and every source-derived row in one planning output.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/05-implement_tables.md`\n  - Fans out one write per planned table.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/10-plan_pages.md`\n  - Requires a multipage plan tied to real endpoints/components.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/11-implement_pages.md`\n  - Fans out one page writer per planned page.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/12-finalize.md`\n  - Goal node writes `_layout` and returns only after table/page outputs.\n\n## Prompt cause vs. structural/runtime cause\n\n### Prompt/model inefficiencies: secondary\n\nThere are recoverable model/protocol slips, but they did not prevent completion:\n\n- `read_sources` made two nullability-invalid `inspect(...text.length)` statements.\n- `plan_endpoints` used prohibited `console.warn`.\n- After the tasklist completed, the automator emitted a prose fragment that was parsed as code and typechecked unsuccessfully.\n\nThese cost retries, but all relevant forks ultimately ended `done`, and the tasklist finished. Tightening prompts or filtering prose could reduce several seconds/minutes, but it does not address the false `built:false` signal or the 11+ minute architecture of the build.\n\n### Structural/runtime cause: primary\n\n1. **The appbuilder is intrinsically large for this input.**  \n   The 12-stage DAG has serialized model-planning gates and a four-way concurrency cap. `runTasklist()` waits for each ready batch before exposing its outputs to the next stage:\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/tasklist/orchestrator.ts` — `runTasklist()`, especially ready-batch execution around lines 155–323.\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/fork/fork.ts` — `ForkEngine.acquireSlot()` and default per-fork execution.  \n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/session/session.ts` — `Session.getForkEngine()` defaults `maxConcurrentForks` to 4.\n\n2. **The trace’s `built` field is not an authoring-completion field.**  \n   Scenario snapshot reads `GET /app`, and records `man.build?.built`:\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/run-yaml.mjs` — `snapshot()`, lines 106–124.\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/routes/app-admin.ts` — `pagesBuildInfo()`, lines 547–568: `built` means a pre-existing `.data/pages-dist/index.html`; it does not build.\n   - A build only occurs in scenario step `open_app`:\n     `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/run-yaml.mjs`, lines 258–263, which calls `POST /app/build`.\n   - Hence step 2’s `built:false` is expected until the explicit step-3 build runs, even if pages were fully authored.\n\n3. **The scenario runner treats interruption separately from actual task completion.**\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/lib/thing.mjs` — `ThingSession.#dispatchAndWait()`.\n   - Its intended cap is 20 minutes (`timeoutMs = 1_200_000`), but it returns `interrupted:true` whenever a session disappears after work began. The recorded 910,351 ms interruption is consistent with the pod/session disappearing rather than a `BudgetExceededError`; there is no appbuilder budget-exceeded trace.\n\n4. **Page compilation is deliberately decoupled from writer success.**\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/authoring/globals.ts` — `writeProjectPage()` calls `onAppWrite`, but only after successful source write.\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/session-manager.ts` — `buildProjectAuthoring().onAppWrite()` invalidates contracts/API runtime/page cache; it does not synchronously call `buildProjectPages()`.\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/build/pages.ts` — `buildProjectPages()` is triggered by the build endpoint/lazy serving and is an esbuild/Tailwind operation.\n\n## Lowest-rung recommendation\n\n**Fix the scenario observation/runner first, not the appbuilder prompt or DAG.**\n\nAt the step-2 snapshot boundary, either:\n\n1. invoke `POST /api/projects/<id>/app/build` before asserting `appManifest.built`; or\n2. change the step-2 assertion to treat authored `pages` plus a successful tasklist finalization as the app-authoring completion signal, reserving `build.built` for the explicit `open_app` step.\n\nThis is the smallest correct fix because the app did author correctly and step 3 already validates compilation/serving. It prevents a false negative without increasing LLM cost or changing the appbuilder’s output contract.\n\nIf wall-clock margin remains a problem after fixing observation, next rung is to run appbuilding separately from the three specialist-space builds (or raise fan-out concurrency for this harness). Do **not** first weaken the binding plan or page/component pipeline: that would trade the current timing artifact for the real empty-app regression the tasklist was designed to prevent.\n\n## Current uncommitted relevant diff\n\nAt repository root:\n\n- Modified: `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/delegation.md`\n  - Documentation-only change describing propagation of `codeNodeCtxFactory` into delegated tasklists.\n- Modified gitlink: `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org`\n  - Advances from `cc1335ae` to `bcbc065`.\n  - The new SDK commit changes `implement_tables` from a deterministic code node back to a model task:\n    - replaces `libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/05-implement_tables.ts`\n    - adds `libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/05-implement_tables.md`\n  - This increases model turns relative to the prior code-node implementation and is relevant to runtime, but it is **not the cause of the observed `built:false`**.\n\nNo uncommitted changes were found inside the checked-out `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org` worktree itself. The remaining root changes are scenario-run artifacts/deletions and untracked round-2 evidence; they do not modify appbuilder/runtime source.","usage":{"total_tokens":0,"tool_uses":87,"duration_ms":248598},"uuid":"009d80fe-dbc9-4c7e-a00a-25887e221936","session_id":"10d74089-d65b-435d-a979-1d29f6775b52"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_sc8TxR4N98D3JKwXfOKvuRrQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Finding\n\nThis was **not an app-authoring failure**. The automator completed the full live-project pipeline; the observed `appManifest.built: false` is a **snapshot/build-status timing artifact**, while the harness marked the overall turn interrupted just before its 20-minute cap.\n\n### Trace evidence\n\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/2/06-tanzania/step-02.full.json`\n  - Records the outer turn as `durationMs: 910351`, `interrupted: true`, before the harness’s normal 1,200,000 ms cap.\n  - State already has six populated tables and page routes, but snapshot sets `\"built\": false`.\n  - The tasklist’s source trace is:\n    `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/sessions/6d75160f-373d-4904-bfe8-38b990da1f8c/trace.json`\n    - `tasklist:build_live_project` completed in **671,325 ms**.\n    - `delegate:system-appbuilder/automator/build_live_project` completed in **683,686 ms**.\n    - It wrote **9 normal pages plus `_layout`** and completed `finalize`.\n    - Tasklist model work: **53 LLM responses**, about **286,606 input** and **38,667 output tokens**.\n    - The parent `organize_material` tasklist took **923,980 ms** because it also built the three specialist spaces. The overall session then ended error/interrupted around **943,507 ms**.\n\n- The same round’s step 3 proves the authored app was buildable:\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/2/06-tanzania/step-03.full.json`\n  - `POST /app/build` reports `built: true`, six routes, and root page HTTP 200.\n  - Therefore `built:false` at step 2 does not mean the automator omitted pages or produced an invalid app.\n\n- The generated project currently contains all necessary artifacts:\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/database/`\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/api/`\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/components/`\n  - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/pages/`\n  - It also now has `.data/pages-dist/index.html` and `.data/pages-cache.json`.\n\n## Where time goes\n\nThe expensive portion is structurally expected model work, not the writers:\n\n| Phase | Trace duration | Notes |\n|---|---:|---|\n| `read_sources` | 97.6 s | 15 model responses, plus two recoverable nullability typecheck retries |\n| `plan_tables` | 263.2 s | Dominant appbuilder node; source-derived schemas and all rows for six tables |\n| `implement_tables` | 9.1 s aggregate wall completion | Six concurrent per-table writers |\n| `plan_endpoints` | 25.3 s | One recoverable `console.warn` typecheck retry |\n| `implement_endpoints` | 58.9 s aggregate wall completion | 13 per-endpoint model writers |\n| `plan_components` | 58.9 s | Runs once endpoints are available |\n| `implement_components` | 78.6 s aggregate wall completion | Six writers |\n| `plan_pages` | 78.6 s | Depends on component plan/endpoints |\n| `implement_pages` | 64.1 s aggregate wall completion | Nine page writers |\n| `finalize` | 4.7 s | Writes `_layout`/Chat dock and resolves |\n\nThe outer tasklist is serial at phase boundaries (`read → stories → app plan → tables → endpoints → components → pages → finalize`) and the shared `ForkEngine` caps each fan-out to **four concurrent forks**. The Tanzania request induced six tables, 13 endpoints, six components, and nine content pages, so the pipeline necessarily queues multiple batches.\n\nRelevant structure:\n\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/index.md`\n  - Explicitly specifies a complete, per-item plan/build pipeline.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/04-plan_tables.md`\n  - Requires every table schema and every source-derived row in one planning output.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/05-implement_tables.md`\n  - Fans out one write per planned table.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/10-plan_pages.md`\n  - Requires a multipage plan tied to real endpoints/components.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/11-implement_pages.md`\n  - Fans out one page writer per planned page.\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/dist/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/12-finalize.md`\n  - Goal node writes `_layout` and returns only after table/page outputs.\n\n## Prompt cause vs. structural/runtime cause\n\n### Prompt/model inefficiencies: secondary\n\nThere are recoverable model/protocol slips, but they did not prevent completion:\n\n- `read_sources` made two nullability-invalid `inspect(...text.length)` statements.\n- `plan_endpoints` used prohibited `console.warn`.\n- After the tasklist completed, the automator emitted a prose fragment that was parsed as code and typechecked unsuccessfully.\n\nThese cost retries, but all relevant forks ultimately ended `done`, and the tasklist finished. Tightening prompts or filtering prose could reduce several seconds/minutes, but it does not address the false `built:false` signal or the 11+ minute architecture of the build.\n\n### Structural/runtime cause: primary\n\n1. **The appbuilder is intrinsically large for this input.**  \n   The 12-stage DAG has serialized model-planning gates and a four-way concurrency cap. `runTasklist()` waits for each ready batch before exposing its outputs to the next stage:\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/tasklist/orchestrator.ts` — `runTasklist()`, especially ready-batch execution around lines 155–323.\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/fork/fork.ts` — `ForkEngine.acquireSlot()` and default per-fork execution.  \n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/src/session/session.ts` — `Session.getForkEngine()` defaults `maxConcurrentForks` to 4.\n\n2. **The trace’s `built` field is not an authoring-completion field.**  \n   Scenario snapshot reads `GET /app`, and records `man.build?.built`:\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/run-yaml.mjs` — `snapshot()`, lines 106–124.\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/routes/app-admin.ts` — `pagesBuildInfo()`, lines 547–568: `built` means a pre-existing `.data/pages-dist/index.html`; it does not build.\n   - A build only occurs in scenario step `open_app`:\n     `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/run-yaml.mjs`, lines 258–263, which calls `POST /app/build`.\n   - Hence step 2’s `built:false` is expected until the explicit step-3 build runs, even if pages were fully authored.\n\n3. **The scenario runner treats interruption separately from actual task completion.**\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/lib/thing.mjs` — `ThingSession.#dispatchAndWait()`.\n   - Its intended cap is 20 minutes (`timeoutMs = 1_200_000`), but it returns `interrupted:true` whenever a session disappears after work began. The recorded 910,351 ms interruption is consistent with the pod/session disappearing rather than a `BudgetExceededError`; there is no appbuilder budget-exceeded trace.\n\n4. **Page compilation is deliberately decoupled from writer success.**\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/authoring/globals.ts` — `writeProjectPage()` calls `onAppWrite`, but only after successful source write.\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/server/session-manager.ts` — `buildProjectAuthoring().onAppWrite()` invalidates contracts/API runtime/page cache; it does not synchronously call `buildProjectPages()`.\n   - `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/build/pages.ts` — `buildProjectPages()` is triggered by the build endpoint/lazy serving and is an esbuild/Tailwind operation.\n\n## Lowest-rung recommendation\n\n**Fix the scenario observation/runner first, not the appbuilder prompt or DAG.**\n\nAt the step-2 snapshot boundary, either:\n\n1. invoke `POST /api/projects/<id>/app/build` before asserting `appManifest.built`; or\n2. change the step-2 assertion to treat authored `pages` plus a successful tasklist finalization as the app-authoring completion signal, reserving `build.built` for the explicit `open_app` step.\n\nThis is the smallest correct fix because the app did author correctly and step 3 already validates compilation/serving. It prevents a false negative without increasing LLM cost or changing the appbuilder’s output contract.\n\nIf wall-clock margin remains a problem after fixing observation, next rung is to run appbuilding separately from the three specialist-space builds (or raise fan-out concurrency for this harness). Do **not** first weaken the binding plan or page/component pipeline: that would trade the current timing artifact for the real empty-app regression the tasklist was designed to prevent.\n\n## Current uncommitted relevant diff\n\nAt repository root:\n\n- Modified: `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/org/docs/runtime/delegation.md`\n  - Documentation-only change describing propagation of `codeNodeCtxFactory` into delegated tasklists.\n- Modified gitlink: `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org`\n  - Advances from `cc1335ae` to `bcbc065`.\n  - The new SDK commit changes `implement_tables` from a deterministic code node back to a model task:\n    - r