{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_m81XkW2Ey2hGiDBSdl5tAE4a","type":"tool_result","content":"Context variables (available in scope):\n- query: \"Organize all of this Tanzania trip material into an app the user can open and check on their phone. The trip is Aug 3–20, 2026, with 8 itinerary legs, costs, park fees, personal notes, a Stone Town photo, and voice-memo details from the Ngorongoro crater day.\\n\\nBuild the complete live-project app now: write source-derived tables and rows, then write the project API and openable pages that show those rows.\\n\\nSource summary:\\nA Tanzania trip (Aug 3–20, 2026) spread across: a multi-sheet spreadsheet with 8 itinerary legs and cost breakdown; a personal notes file covering several Tanzania topics; the official Ngorongoro Conservation Area park-fee PDF; a Stone Town Zanzibar courtyard photo; and a voice memo from the Ngorongoro crater day with driver details, a Maasai bracelet purchase, and a question about an extra ranger tip.\\n\\nFacts available only from image/audio analysis:\\n\\nVOICE MEMO (transcript — crater day, user recorded at the rim):\\n- Driver-guide at Ngorongoro Crater: Emmanuel (not Richard from the office). Knew his stuff — spotted wildlife before we saw it.\\n- Bought two beaded bracelets from a Maasai lady at the rim for Athena Mari.\\n- Price: roughly $20-25 USD, or about TZS 35,000. Exact amount uncertain — user paid in shillings and didn't write it down.\\n- Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip sometimes expected at the gate: TZS 5,000, cash, separate from park fees. Nobody told the user about this before.\\n- Action item: ask Richard about the ranger tip before the safari balance payment.\\n\\nIMAGE (stone-town-zanzibar.jpg — user's photo):\\nThis photo shows a bright courtyard framed by a white Mediterranean-style building with multiple arched windows and dark carved wooden balconies stacked above each other. It appears to be taken from below inside the courtyard, looking up toward a clear blue sky. The ornate balcony railings and sunlit walls stand out most visually, giving it a warm, historic travel feel.\\n\\n\\nSpecialist build results:\\n[{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Tanzania trip itinerary & logistics (Aug 3–20, 2026)\\\",\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"errors\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Ngorongoro Crater safari day — driver, fees, and tips\\\",\\\"ok\\\":false,\\\"errors\\\":\\\"Function 'validateSpace' is not defined in this execution context. It must be provided by the host as a global binding before this script runs. Available globals in this EXPLORE subagent: sleep, display, loadKnowledge, inspect, fetch, currentTask, seed (and design, topic, goal, research inputs). No validateSpace, readFile, grep, glob, listDir, webSearch, or webFetch are present.; Function 'validateSpace' is not defined in this execution context. It must be provided by the host as a global binding before this script runs. Available globals in this EXPLORE subagent: sleep, display, loadKnowledge, inspect, fetch, currentTask, seed (and design, topic, goal, research inputs). No validateSpace, readFile, grep, glob, listDir, webSearch, or webFetch are present.\\\"},{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Local purchases, currency, and cultural customs in Tanzania\\\",\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"errors\\\":\\\"\\\"},{\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Stone Town, Zanzibar — destination orientation\\\",\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"errors\\\":\\\"\\\"}]\"\n- attachmentIds: [\"eb45524a-d710-44fe-a637-692aa522664e\",\"d8e57418-07fb-47a4-bb50-a9d394bab81e\",\"f1867b8c-cbe8-44e9-b4e6-f9e74c861aa0\",\"4d3d3b5d-57fb-4180-b8b8-e855b1c4ed70\"]\nInputs from upstream tasks (available as variables):\n- plan_app: {\"title\":\"Tanzania Trip 2026 — Kilimanjaro to Zanzibar\",\"purpose\":\"A mobile-first trip companion app to check itinerary, costs, park fees, contacts, personal notes, and a photo gallery for an Aug 3–20, 2026 Tanzania safari + Zanzibar journey.\",\"tables\":[{\"name\":\"travelers\",\"purpose\":\"2 traveler records (Vasilis, Athina Mari) — serves see-contact-info and contextualizes all personal notes and purchases across the trip.\"},{\"name\":\"contacts\",\"purpose\":\"2 contact records — Richard (safari operator/office) and Emmanuel (Ngorongoro driver-guide) — serves see-contact-info and resolve-ranger-tip-question.\"},{\"name\":\"itinerary_legs\",\"purpose\":\"8 chronological legs from Cairo (Aug 3–5) through Zanzibar/Stone Town (Aug 15–20) with date range, nights, hotel, and lodging cost — serves see-full-itinerary-in-order, glance-at-dashboard-for-whats-next, and anchors all leg-tagged notes and photos.\"},{\"name\":\"costs\",\"purpose\":\"10 line-item cost rows with category, amount, status (paid/pending/estimate) — serves review-all-costs-and-total-budget and glance-at-dashboard-for-whats-next.\"},{\"name\":\"park_fees\",\"purpose\":\"2 official Ngorongoro Conservation Area tariff rows from PDF (adult entry permit $70.80/24hrs, crater service fee $295/descent) — serves check-park-fees-and-rules and cross-references costs table.\"},{\"name\":\"voice_memo_notes\",\"purpose\":\"3 notes from the Ngorongoro crater rim recording — driver ID (Emmanuel), bracelet purchase ($20-25/TZS 35,000 for Athina Mari), ranger-tip action item (TZS 5,000 unpaid tip disclosure) — serves resolve-ranger-tip-question and log-bracelet-purchase-and-other-personal-notes.\"},{\"name\":\"photo_gallery\",\"purpose\":\"1 photo row — the Stone Town Zanzibar courtyard image with caption and leg-8 location context — serves browse-stone-town-photo-and-gallery.\"}],\"endpoints\":[{\"route\":\"itinerary-legs-list/GET\",\"purpose\":\"Returns all 8 itinerary legs sorted chronologically with their date ranges, nights, hotel names, and lodging costs for the full-trip list view.\"},{\"route\":\"costs-all/GET\",\"purpose\":\"Returns all 10 cost rows plus computed grand total ($8,217) and subtotals (bulk $6,800 flights+safari, remainder $1,417) for the budget review page.\"},{\"route\":\"park-fees-list/GET\",\"purpose\":\"Returns the 2 official Ngorongoro park-fee tariff rows with cross-reference links to the matching costs table entries (entry permits ×2, service fee).\"},{\"route\":\"contacts-list/GET\",\"purpose\":\"Returns both contact records (Richard and Emmanuel) with their roles and linked action items.\"},{\"route\":\"notes-by-leg/GET\",\"purpose\":\"Returns voice_memo_notes filtered by itinerary leg (e.g. leg 5, Ngorongoro Crater Aug 10–12) plus any user-added notes for log-bracelet-purchase-and-other-personal-notes.\"},{\"route\":\"photo-gallery-all/GET\",\"purpose\":\"Returns the photo gallery rows (starting with the 1 Stone Town courtyard image) linked to their itinerary legs for the gallery and detail views.\"}],\"components\":[{\"name\":\"ItineraryLegCard\",\"purpose\":\"A tappable card showing one itinerary leg: location name, date range, nights count, hotel name, and lodging cost. Expands inline to reveal full details. Reused in the itinerary list and dashboard next-leg preview.\"},{\"name\":\"CostRow\",\"purpose\":\"A compact line-item row showing a cost category, its dollar amount, and a paid/pending/estimate status badge. Reused in the costs full list and the dashboard budget summary.\"},{\"name\":\"ActionItemCard\",\"purpose\":\"A highlighted card for an open to-do: shows the action text (e.g. \\\"Ask Richard about ranger tip — TZS 5,000\\\"), a linked contact, and a tap-to-resolve toggle. Reused on the notes page, the Ngorongoro detail, and the dashboard.\"},{\"name\":\"PhotoCard\",\"purpose\":\"A thumbnail card showing a travel photo with caption, linked leg label, and tap-to-expand. Reused in the gallery grid and on the Zanzibar leg detail page.\"},{\"name\":\"DashboardStat\",\"purpose\":\"A small summary number-card showing a key figure — next leg in days, pending action-item count, or remaining budget buffer. Reused in the dashboard and as a header strip on key pages.\"}],\"pages\":[{\"route\":\"index\",\"purpose\":\"The dashboard home — shows the nea