", \"tables\": [\"park_fees\", \"costs\"]}, {\"name\": \"contacts-all\", \"route\": \"contacts/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns both contact records — Richard (safari operator) and Emmanuel (driver-guide) — with their roles, details, and any linked_action text, plus the associated traveler name if applicable.\", \"tables\": [\"contacts\", \"travelers\"]}, {\"name\": \"notes-by-leg\", \"route\": \"notes/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns voice_memo_notes filtered by an optional ?leg_id= query parameter; includes note_type, content, linked contact name, linked traveler name, and resolved status. Powers the notes section on the leg-detail page and the personal-notes list.\", \"tables\": [\"voice_memo_notes\", \"contacts\", \"travelers\", \"itinerary_legs\"]}, {\"name\": \"notes-action-items\", \"route\": \"notes/action-items/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns only unresolved action_item notes (currently note-3 about the ranger tip) with linked contact and leg context — powers the dashboard pending-action count and the action-item cards list.\", \"tables\": [\"voice_memo_notes\", \"contacts\", \"itinerary_legs\"]}, {\"name\": \"photo-gallery-all\", \"route\": \"photos/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns all photo_gallery rows (starting with the 1 Stone Town courtyard image) with caption, image_ref, leg location, and taken_by, joined to itinerary_legs for the leg label — powers the gallery grid page and the photos section on leg-detail.\", \"tables\": [\"photo_gallery\", \"itinerary_legs\"]}, {\"name\": \"dashboard-summary\", \"route\": \"dashboard/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Composite endpoint returning the nearest upcoming itinerary leg, count of unresolved action items, and the budget grand-total with remaining buffer — a single lightweight fetch for the dashboard home page.\", \"tables\": [\"itinerary_legs\", \"voice_memo_notes\", \"costs\"]}]}\nEND 1959 task_200_0cb3409d {\"ok\": true, \"tables\": [\"travelers\", \"contacts\", \"itinerary_legs\", \"costs\", \"park_fees\", \"voice_memo_notes\", \"photo_gallery\"], \"endpoints\": [\"itinerary-legs/GET\", \"itinerary-legs/[id]/GET\", \"costs/GET\", \"park-fees/GET\", \"contacts/GET\", \"notes/GET\", \"notes/action-items/GET\", \"photos/GET\", \"dashboard/GET\"], \"components\": [\"ItineraryLegCard\", \"CostRow\", \"ActionItemCard\", \"PhotoCard\", \"DashboardStat\"], \"pages\": [\"index\", \"itinerary\", \"costs\", \"gallery\", \"contacts\", \"notes\", \"_layout\"]}\nEND 1975 task_122_3f958b51 {\"ok\": true, \"detail\": \"{\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"tables\\\":[\\\"travelers\\\",\\\"contacts\\\",\\\"itinerary_legs\\\",\\\"costs\\\",\\\"park_fees\\\",\\\"voice_memo_notes\\\",\\\"photo_gallery\\\"],\\\"endpoints\\\":[\\\"itinerary-legs/GET\\\",\\\"itinerary-legs/[id]/GET\\\",\\\"costs/GET\\\",\\\"park-fees/GET\\\",\\\"contacts/GET\\\",\\\"notes/GET\\\",\\\"notes/action-items/GET\\\",\\\"photos/GET\\\",\\\"dashboard/GET\\\"],\\\"components\\\":[\\\"ItineraryLegCard\\\",\\\"CostRow\\\",\\\"ActionItemCard\\\",\\\"PhotoCard\\\",\\\"DashboardStat\\\"],\\\"pages\\\":[\\\"index\\\",\\\"itinerary\\\",\\\"costs\\\",\\\"gallery\\\",\\\"contacts\\\",\\\"notes\\\",\\\"_layout\\\"]}\"}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"10d74089-d65b-435d-a979-1d29f6775b52","uuid":"6bad2dc1-a7bb-4e63-b265-30ef444869f1","timestamp":"2026-07-16T22:50:24.355Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"END 1340 task_126_f67bc54b {\"summary\": \"TANZANIA TRIP APP — COMPLETE BUILD BRIEF (Aug 3–20, 2026)\\n\\nTRAVELERS: Vasilis (primary) + Athina Mari (companion)\\n\\nCONTACTS:\\n- Richard — safari operator / office contact. Quoted the 7-day northern circuit package. Action: ask him about the extra ranger tip (TZS 5,000) before final safari balance payment.\\n- Emmanuel — actual driver-guide at Ngorongoro Crater (not Richard). Skilled spotter; well-regarded.\\n\\nITINERARY (8 legs, spreadsheet rows):\\n1. Cairo (arrival stopover) | Aug 3–5 | 2 nts | Eileen Hotel | $102\\n2. Arusha (pre-safari) | Aug 5–7 | 2 nts | Serengeti Villa | $140\\n3. Tarangire NP | Aug 7–9 | 2 nts | Sangaiwe Tented Camp | $640\\n4. Lake Manyara | Aug 9–10 | 1 nt | Manyara Wildlife Safari Camp | $320\\n5. Ngorongoro Crater | Aug 10–12 | 2 nts | Rhino Lodge | $480\\n6. Serengeti NP (central) | Aug 12–14 | 2 nts | Serengeti Heritage Camp | $720\\n7. Arusha (post-safari) | Aug 14–15 | 1 nt | Serengeti Villa | $70\\n8. Zanzibar / Stone Town | Aug 15–20 | 5 nts | Emerson Spice Hotel | $900\\nTotal lodging: $3,372\\n\\nCOST BREAKDOWN (spreadsheet \\\"costs\\\" sheet — all rows):\\n- International flights (Cairo + Dar return) | $1,800 est | not yet booked (by Mar 2026)\\n- Tanzania e-visa (×2) | $100 | online before departure\\n- Travel insurance (×2) | $80 | World Nomads or similar\\n- Safari package (7-day northern circuit, 2 pax) | $5,000 | quoted by Richard — includes lodging, meals, guide, vehicle\\n- Ngorongoro crater service fee | $295 | PAID (with package deposit)\\n- Ngorongoro entry permits (×2 at $70.80 each) | $142 | payable at gate in cash USD\\n- Tips & gratuities | $150 | guide $10/day, cook $5/day, rangers\\n- Maasai bracelets & souvenirs | $50 | misc cash purchases\\n- Zanzibar activities & meals | $400 | spice tour, snorkeling, dinners\\n- Misc & buffer | $200 | unexpected costs\\n- GRAND TOTAL: $8,217 (flights + safari = $6,800 bulk; remainder $1,417)\\n\\nNGORONGORO OFFICIAL TARIFFS (from PDF):\\n- Non-East African Citizen entry permit (age 16+): $70.80/person/24hrs\\n- Crater service fee (foreign vehicle, per descent): $295\\n- Children 5–16: $23.60; under 5: free\\n\\nVOICE MEMO FACTS (Ngorongoro crater day, recorded at rim):\\n- Driver: Emmanuel (not Richard). Excellent wildlife spotter.\\n- Purchase: two beaded bracelets from a Maasai lady at the crater rim, for Athina Mari. Price paid in Tanzanian shillings, approx $20–25 USD / TZS 35,000.\\n- Hidden fee: Emmanuel disclosed a ranger tip of TZS 5,000 cash sometimes expected at the gate, separate from park fees. User was not informed beforehand.\\n- Open action: ask Richard about the ranger tip before paying the safari balance.\\n\\nPHOTO (stone-town-zanzibar.jpg):\\n- Subject: interior courtyard of a white Mediterranean-style building in Stone Town. Arched windows, dark carved wooden balconies stacked above, photographed from below looking up toward clear blue sky. Warm sunlit walls, ornate balcony railings. Historic travel aesthetic.\\n- Location: Zanzibar / Stone Town (leg 8: Aug 15–20, Emerson Spice Hotel vicinity).\\n\\nPERSONAL NOTES (tanzaniamemories.md):\\n- Confirms travelers, all 8 legs, hotel names, Richard as operator, the Ngorongoro ranger-tip uncertainty, bracelet purchase, and Stone Town courtyard photo.\\n- Vasilis wants a phone-checkable app showing itinerary, costs, park fees, notes, and the photo.\\n\\nREQUIRED APP TABLES (source-derived rows only — no fabrication):\\n- travelers: 2 rows (Vasilis, Athina Mari)\\n- contacts: 2 rows (Richard — operator, Emmanuel — driver-guide)\\n- itinerary_legs: 8 rows exactly as above\\n- costs: 10 rows exactly as above\\n- park_fees: 2 rows (entry permit adult 16+, crater service fee per vehicle)\\n- voice_memo_notes: 3 rows (driver ID, bracelet purchase, ranger-tip action item)\\n- photo_gallery: 1 row (Stone Town courtyard, leg 8, with image reference)\\n\\nEND BRIEF.\", \"ok\": true}\nSTART 1342 user_stories fork_129_cb1fd4cd\nSTART 1354 plan_app fork_131_9855ef72\nEND 1364 task_130_0a6b369b {\"title\": \"Tanzania Trip 2026 — Kilimanjaro to Zanzibar\", \"purpose\": \"A mobile-first trip companion app to check itinerary, costs, park fees, contacts, personal notes, and a photo gallery for an Aug 3–20, 2026 Tanzania safari + Zanzibar journey.\", \"tables\": [{\"name\": \"travelers\", \"purpose\": \"2 traveler records (Vasilis, Athina Mari) — serves see-contact-info and contextualizes all personal notes and purchases across the trip.\"}, {\"name\": \"contacts\", \"purpose\": \"2 contact records — Richard (safari operator/office) and Emmanuel (Ngorongoro driver-guide) — serves see-contact-info and resolve-ranger-tip-question.\"}, {\"name\": \"itinerary_legs\", \"purpose\": \"8 chronological legs from Cairo (Aug 3–5) through Zanzibar/Stone Town (Aug 15–20) with date range, nights, hotel, and lodging cost — serves see-full-itinerary-in-order, glance-at-dashboard-for-whats-next, and anchors all leg-tagged notes and photos.\"}, {\"name\": \"costs\", \"purpose\": \"10 line-item cost rows with category, amount, status (paid/pending/estimate) — serves review-all-costs-and-total-budget and glance-at-dashboard-for-whats-next.\"}, {\"name\": \"park_fees\", \"purpose\": \"2 official Ngorongoro Conservation Area tariff rows from PDF (adult entry permit $70.80/24hrs, crater service fee $295/descent) — serves check-park-fees-and-rules and cross-references costs table.\"}, {\"name\": \"voice_memo_notes\", \"purpose\": \"3 notes from the Ngorongoro crater rim recording — driver ID (Emmanuel), bracelet purchase ($20-25/TZS 35,000 for Athina Mari), ranger-tip action item (TZS 5,000 unpaid tip disclosure) — serves resolve-ranger-tip-question and log-bracelet-purchase-and-other-personal-notes.\"}, {\"name\": \"photo_gallery\", \"purpose\": \"1 photo row — the Stone Town Zanzibar courtyard image with caption and leg-8 location context — serves browse-stone-town-photo-and-gallery.\"}], \"endpoints\": [{\"route\": \"itinerary-legs-list/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns all 8 itinerary legs sorted chronologically with their date ranges, nights, hotel names, and lodging costs for the full-trip list view.\"}, {\"route\": \"costs-all/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns all 10 cost rows plus computed grand total ($8,217) and subtotals (bulk $6,800 flights+safari, remainder $1,417) for the budget review page.\"}, {\"route\": \"park-fees-list/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns the 2 official Ngorongoro park-fee tariff rows with cross-reference links to the matching costs table entries (entry permits ×2, service fee).\"}, {\"route\": \"contacts-list/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns both contact records (Richard and Emmanuel) with their roles and linked action items.\"}, {\"route\": \"notes-by-leg/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns voice_memo_notes filtered by itinerary leg (e.g. leg 5, Ngorongoro Crater Aug 10–12) plus any user-added notes for log-bracelet-purchase-and-other-personal-notes.\"}, {\"route\": \"photo-gallery-all/GET\", \"purpose\": \"Returns the photo gallery rows (starting with the 1 Stone Town courtyard image) linked to their itinerary legs for the gallery and detail views.\"}], \"components\": [{\"name\": \"ItineraryLegCard\", \"purpose\": \"A tappable card showing one itinerary leg: location name, date range, nights count, hotel name, and lodging cost. Expands inline to reveal full details. Reused in the itinerary list and dashboard next-leg preview.\"}, {\"name\": \"CostRow\", \"purpose\": \"A compact line-item row showing a cost category, its dollar amount, and a paid/pending/estimate status badge. Reused in the costs full list and the dashboard budget summary.\"}, {\"name\": \"ActionItemCard\", \"purpose\": \"A highlighted card for an open to-do: shows the action text (e.g. \\\"Ask Richard about ranger tip — TZS 5,000\\\"), a linked contact, and a tap-to-resolve toggle. Reused on the notes page, the Ngorongoro detail, and the dashboard.\"}, {\"name\": \"PhotoCard\", \"purpose\": \"A thumbnail card showing a travel photo with caption, linked leg label, and tap-to-expand. Reused in the gallery grid and on the Zanzibar leg detail page.\"}, {\"name\": \"DashboardStat\", \"purpose\": \"A small summary number-card showing a key figure — next leg in days, pending action-item count, or remaining budget buffer. Reused in the dashboard and as a header strip on key pages.\"}], \"pages\": [{\"route\": \"index\", \"purpose\": \"The dashboard home — shows the nearest upcoming itinerary leg (via ItineraryLegCard), pending action-item count (via ActionItemCard), and a budget-at-a-glance with grand total and buffer remaining (via Dashboar