{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_tcystY9tXcPg0KwL0MmTDn4s","type":"tool_result","content":"SEQ 1121 node_start fork_100_7da61496\n{\"ts\": 1784242743957, \"type\": \"node_start\", \"nodeId\": \"fork_100_7da61496\", \"parentId\": \"task_99_c5c88fb2\", \"kind\": \"fork\", \"label\": \"fork:read_sources\", \"context\": \"fork:read_sources\", \"status\": \"queued\", \"detail\": {\"role\": \"explore\", \"taskId\": \"read_sources\", \"instruction\": \"Read every supplied document before building. `query`, `attachmentIds`, and `documents` are in\\nscope. The context previe\"}}\nSEQ 1169 node_end task_99_c5c88fb2\n{\"ts\": 1784242867177, \"type\": \"node_end\", \"nodeId\": \"task_99_c5c88fb2\", \"status\": \"done\", \"durationMs\": 123220, \"result\": {\"summary\": \"BUILD BRIEF — Tanzania Trip App (Aug 3–20, 2026)\\n\\nTRAVELERS: Vasilis + Athina Mari (2 adults, non-East African citizens).\\n\\nFLIGHTS: Athens→Cairo→Arusha (Kilimanjaro), return Dar es Salaam→Athens. Total ~€2,700 for both. Internal: Arusha→Zanzibar (Precision Air, ~$250 total), Zanzibar→Dar es Salaam (ferry, ~$70 total).\\n\\nITINERARY (leg-by-leg from spreadsheet \\\"legs\\\" sheet):\\n1. Cairo stopover: Aug 3–5, 2 nights, Eileen Hotel, $102\\n2. Arusha pre-safari: Aug 5–7, 2 nights, Serengeti Villa, $160\\n3. Safari Day 1 – Tarangire: Aug 7–8, 1 night, Serengeti Heritage Luxury Camps, $540\\n4. Safari Day 2 – Lake Manyara: Aug 8–9, 1 night, Serengeti Heritage Luxury Camps, $540\\n5. Safari Day 3 – Ngorongoro Crater: Aug 9–10, 1 night, Serengeti Heritage Luxury Camps, $540\\n6. Arusha post-safari: Aug 10–11, 1 night, Serengeti Villa, $80\\n7. Zanzibar – Stone Town: Aug 11–14, 3 nights, Kholle House, $324\\n8. Zanzibar – Paje Beach: Aug 14–18, 4 nights, Paje Blu, $400\\n9. Dar es Salaam departure: Aug 18–20, 2 nights, Tidel Hotel, $160\\nSAFARI PACKAGE: 3-day/3-night Safari (Tarangire, Manyara, Ngorongoro) with Serengeti Heritage — cost $1,320 (covers vehicle, driver-guide, accommodation, meals, park fees). Booked with Richard.\\nTOTAL LODGING + SAFARI (spreadsheet): $2,846\\n\\nCOST BREAKDOWN (from spreadsheet \\\"cost-summary\\\" sheet):\\n- Flights (international): €2,700 (~$2,970 at €1=$1.10)\\n- Visa (Tanzania, 2 pax): $100\\n- Cairo (Eileen Hotel 2 nights): $102\\n- Arusha pre+post (Serengeti Villa 3 nights): $240\\n- Safari package (3 days, Tarangire/Manyara/Ngorongoro): $1,320\\n- Zanzibar Stone Town (Kholle House 3 nights): $324\\n- Zanzibar Paje (Paje Blu 4 nights): $400\\n- Dar es Salaam (Tidel Hotel 2 nights): $160\\n- Internal transport (Arusha→Zanzibar flight + Zanzibar→Dar ferry): ~$320\\n- Tips & extras budget: ~$300\\nGRAND TOTAL (USD est.): ~$5,936 (lodging + safari $2,846 + flights ~$2,970 + internal transport ~$320 + visas $100 + tips ~$300 = ~$6,536; verify spreadsheet summation)\\n\\nNGORONGORO TARIFFS (from PDF — non-East African citizens):\\n- Entry permit adult (16+): $50 per person per 12 hours (peak), $40 (low season, Apr–May)\\n- Entry permit child (5–16): $15 per person per 12 hours (peak), $10 (low season)\\n- Children under 5: free\\n- Vehicle permit (foreign-registered, up to 2,000cc): $15 per vehicle per 12 hours\\n- Vehicle permit (2,001–4,000cc): $35 per vehicle per 12 hours\\n- Vehicle permit (4,001–7,000cc): $70 per vehicle per 12 hours\\n- Camping fee (public campsite, adult): $40 per person per night peak, $30 low season\\n- Camping fee (public campsite, child): $10 per person per night\\n- Special campsite: $70 per person per night peak\\n- Ranger/guide fee: $30 per group per trek\\n- Walking safari: $50 per person (half-day), $80 (full-day)\\n- Crater service fee: $300 per vehicle per descent (non-commercial)\\n- Horse riding: $60 per person per 2 hours\\n- Filming permit: $400 per camera\\nNOTE: Aug 2026 is peak season — use peak rates. Vasilis + Athina Mari are 2 adults (non-EAC). Entry: 2×$50=$100. Crater descent service fee: $300/vehicle.\\n\\nVOICE MEMO FACTS (Ngorongoro crater day):\\n- Driver-guide name: Emmanuel (not Richard from the booking office)\\n- A Maasai lady at the crater rim sold 2 beaded bracelets for Athina Mari\\n- Price paid: ~TZS 35,000 (approx $20–25 USD), paid in Tanzanian shillings, exact amount uncertain\\n- Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~TZS 5,000 cash at the gate, separate from park fees\\n- User MUST confirm the ranger tip with Richard before paying the safari balance\\n- The bracelet transaction and ranger tip are cash items NOT in the spreadsheet\\n\\nSTONE TOWN PHOTO (image analysis):\\n- Bright courtyard view looking upward at a multi-story white building\\n- Arched windows, dark wooden balconies, decorative railings against blue sky\\n- Classic Zanzibar / Stone Town architecture\\n- Likely at or near Kholle House (the booked Stone Town lodging)\\n\\nCONTACTS:\\n- Richard (booking office, Serengeti Heritage) — handles safari package, needs confirmation on ranger tip\\n- Emmanuel (driver-guide for safari, specifically crater day)\\n\\nDATA TABLES NEEDED:\\n- trips: master trip record (title, dates, travelers, status)\\n- legs: itinerary legs with dates, nights, lodging, cost, notes\\n- costs: line-item cost breakdown by category\\n- contacts: Richard, Emmanuel\\n- ngorongoro_tariffs: park fee rates (from PDF)\\n- trip_notes: free-form notes/observations per leg or day\\n- purchases: bracelet purchase record (crater day)\\n- media: Stone Town photo reference\\n\\nEVENTS & API:\\n- project/db.trips events for CRUD\\n- project/db.legs events with trip_id FK\\n- project/costs events\\n- Read API endpoints exposing joined trip+legs+costs\\n- Pages: Trip Overview (itinerary timeline), Cost Breakdown, Ngorongoro Details, Stone Town, Contact List\\n\\nKEY AMBIGUITIES TO FLAG IN UI:\\n- Bracelet cost: \\\"~TZS 35,000 ($20–25)\\\" marked as approximate\\n- Ranger tip: \\\"~TZS 5,000 — CONFIRM WITH RICHARD\\\" marked as pending\\n- Spreadsheet total vs. summed line items may differ — verify\", \"ok\": true}}\nSEQ 18