{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_MVEqWITRMcMjZgDEhT4X3YMw","type":"tool_result","content":"sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/database/contacts.json:3:  \"description\": \"Key contacts for the safari and trip logistics — the safari company office (Richard) and the driver/guide (Emmanuel).\",\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/game-drives/index.md:6:Game drives form the core of the northern Tanzania safari experience. The Ngorongoro Crater day is a self-contained descent into a wildlife-rich caldera, often led by a dedicated driver-guide like Emmanuel who knows animal movements and facilitates unscheduled stops (e.g., the crater-rim Maasai market for beaded bracelets at ~$20–25 USD / ~35,000 TZS). The Serengeti circuit is a longer, multi-day traverse across vast plains as part of a safari circuit typically linking Arusha, Ngorongoro, the Serengeti, and onward to Zanzibar. Both aspects rely on the driver-guide's field expertise — spotting wildlife, navigating unpaved tracks, and managing the rhythm of the day — entirely separate from the office contact's booking and payment role.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-advisor/knowledge/ngorongoro/regulations/visitor-conduct.md:5:A known informal convention at the descent gate involves a ranger tip of approximately 5,000 TZS, which is not listed anywhere in the official NCAA tariff PDF. This tip is entirely separate from the mandatory park fees and is not a government charge. Visitors are under no obligation to pay it, though it is commonly requested. When reviewing a safari invoice, non-East African visitors should verify that line items match the published NCAA tariff rates and that informal tips are clearly distinguished from compulsory fees.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/trip/legs/arusha-pre-safari.md:3:The Arusha pre-safari leg is the arrival and staging point before heading into the bush. Vasilis stayed at Serengeti Villa in Arusha, a common choice for safari-goers needing a comfortable overnight near Kilimanjaro International Airport before the long drive west toward the Ngorongoro Crater and Serengeti. Arusha serves as the safari hub for northern Tanzania — most operators are based here, and it's where you meet your office contact (like Richard) and your driver-guide (like Emmanuel) to settle payments, review the itinerary, and load the vehicle. Expect to handle any balance payments, confirm cash needs for tips and gate fees, and do a gear check here. The drive from Arusha to Ngorongoro takes roughly 3–4 hours, with the road climbing through farmland and forested highlands before reaching the crater rim.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-advisor/knowledge/ngorongoro/regulations/index.md:6:The Ngorongoro Conservation Area operates under a structured system of official regulations enforced by the NCAA. Park rules establish the formal framework: entry permits are mandatory for every visitor, with age-banded pricing for non-East African citizens drawn from the official tariff schedule. Visitor conduct rules distinguish official NCAA charges from informal gate conventions — such as the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip — which are not part of the published schedule and should not be confused with mandatory fees. Vehicle restrictions apply within the crater and conservation area, governing which vehicles may descend, permitted hours, and associated vehicle fees that sit alongside entry and conservation charges in the tariff PDF. These three facets together define what every non-East African visitor must comply with versus what is discretionary or operator-driven.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/game-drives/ngorongoro-crater.md:3:The Ngorongoro Crater is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the most concentrated wildlife-viewing areas in Africa. A typical crater game drive starts early from a nearby lodge or campsite (often on the rim), with your driver-guide navigating the steep descent road into the caldera floor. Inside, you can expect to see the Big Five — lion, leopard, elephant, buffalo, and the critically endangered black rhino — often within a single morning. Your driver-guide (such as Emmanuel, cited in Vasilis's trip logs as \"really knowledgeable\") handles vehicle positioning, animal-spotting, and commentary. The day typically includes a picnic lunch at a designated spot on the crater floor (hippos may wander nearby), then an afternoon climb back to the rim. Unscheduled stops are common: Emmanuel facilitated a crater-rim stop where Vasilis bought two Maasai beaded bracelets for ~$20–25 USD (~35,000 TZS). Note that a separate ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash is expected at the Ngorongoro gate — an unwritten convention distinct from the park entry fee and safari cost. Confirm this with your office contact (Richard) before final payment.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/cash-conventions/village-market-stops.md:3:Emmanuel also facilitated a stop at the crater rim where Vasilis bought two Maasai beaded bracelets for Athina Mari, ~$20–25 USD / ~35,000 TZS (source: specialistFacts voice memo)\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-advisor/knowledge/ngorongoro/tariffs/entry-permits.md:9:These fees are payable in USD for non-East African visitors, reflecting the expectation of foreign currency payment at the gate. The entry permit is completely separate from safari company costs (vehicle hire, guide, accommodation) and informal tips such as the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip sometimes requested at the crater gate.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/database/notes.json:3:  \"description\": \"Personal notes and trip memories — the Stone Town Zanzibar courtyard, Ngorongoro voice-memo facts about Emmanuel and the Maasai bracelets, and the open action item to ask Richard about the ranger tip.\",\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/office-contact.md:7:- **Pre-trip questions**: serving as the go-to person for logistical clarifications before you meet your guide — including any unwritten cash conventions like ranger tips (ask Richard about the ~5,000 TZS Ngorongoro ranger tip before paying the balance, to avoid surprises).\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/index.md:6:Safari logistics in northern Tanzania split between two distinct roles. The office contact (like Richard) handles commercial coordination: booking confirmations, balance payments, and pre-trip communication. The driver-guide (like Emmanuel) is the field expert — a knowledgeable professional who runs the actual game drives, navigates the parks, and provides on-the-ground interpretation. These roles are separate people with different responsibilities, and understanding this split helps avoid confusion about who to ask for what.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/driver-guide.md:3:The driver-guide is your on-the-ground expert throughout the safari. In Vasilis's arrangement, Emmanuel fills this role, and he is described as 'really knowledgeable.' Key responsibilities include:\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/driver-guide.md:6:- **Park navigation**: handling park entries, gate procedures, and inside-the-park logistics — including knowing unwritten conventions like the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip sometimes expected at Ngorongoro gate.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/driver-guide.md:7:- **Cultural facilitation**: Emmanuel also facilitated a stop at the Ngorongoro crater rim where Vasilis bought Maasai beaded bracelets (~$20–25 USD / ~35,000 TZS), showing how driver-guides often connect travelers with local vendors.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/cash-conventions/index.md:6:Northern Tanzania safaris involve unwritten cash conventions that go beyond quoted safari costs. Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash expected at the Ngorongoro gate, separate from park fees — this is an unwritten convention (source: specialistFacts voice memo) Action item: ask Richard about the ranger tip before paying the safari balance, to avoid surprises (source: specialistFacts voice memo) Emmanuel also facilitated a stop at the crater rim where Vasilis bought two Maasai beaded bracelets for Athina Mari, ~$20–25 USD / ~35,000 TZS (source: specialistFacts voice memo) Understanding these before final safari payment avoids surprises.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/cash-conventions/ranger-tips.md:3:Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash expected at the Ngorongoro gate, separate from park fees — this is an unwritten convention (source: specialistFacts voice memo)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"10d74089-d65b-435d-a979-1d29f6775b52","uuid":"1b73e4f9-9724-401c-820f-83d5f64ed08c","timestamp":"2026-07-16T23:25:17.248Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/database/contacts.json:3:  \"description\": \"Key contacts for the safari and trip logistics — the safari company office (Richard) and the driver/guide (Emmanuel).\",\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/game-drives/index.md:6:Game drives form the core of the northern Tanzania safari experience. The Ngorongoro Crater day is a self-contained descent into a wildlife-rich caldera, often led by a dedicated driver-guide like Emmanuel who knows animal movements and facilitates unscheduled stops (e.g., the crater-rim Maasai market for beaded bracelets at ~$20–25 USD / ~35,000 TZS). The Serengeti circuit is a longer, multi-day traverse across vast plains as part of a safari circuit typically linking Arusha, Ngorongoro, the Serengeti, and onward to Zanzibar. Both aspects rely on the driver-guide's field expertise — spotting wildlife, navigating unpaved tracks, and managing the rhythm of the day — entirely separate from the office contact's booking and payment role.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-advisor/knowledge/ngorongoro/regulations/visitor-conduct.md:5:A known informal convention at the descent gate involves a ranger tip of approximately 5,000 TZS, which is not listed anywhere in the official NCAA tariff PDF. This tip is entirely separate from the mandatory park fees and is not a government charge. Visitors are under no obligation to pay it, though it is commonly requested. When reviewing a safari invoice, non-East African visitors should verify that line items match the published NCAA tariff rates and that informal tips are clearly distinguished from compulsory fees.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/trip/legs/arusha-pre-safari.md:3:The Arusha pre-safari leg is the arrival and staging point before heading into the bush. Vasilis stayed at Serengeti Villa in Arusha, a common choice for safari-goers needing a comfortable overnight near Kilimanjaro International Airport before the long drive west toward the Ngorongoro Crater and Serengeti. Arusha serves as the safari hub for northern Tanzania — most operators are based here, and it's where you meet your office contact (like Richard) and your driver-guide (like Emmanuel) to settle payments, review the itinerary, and load the vehicle. Expect to handle any balance payments, confirm cash needs for tips and gate fees, and do a gear check here. The drive from Arusha to Ngorongoro takes roughly 3–4 hours, with the road climbing through farmland and forested highlands before reaching the crater rim.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-advisor/knowledge/ngorongoro/regulations/index.md:6:The Ngorongoro Conservation Area operates under a structured system of official regulations enforced by the NCAA. Park rules establish the formal framework: entry permits are mandatory for every visitor, with age-banded pricing for non-East African citizens drawn from the official tariff schedule. Visitor conduct rules distinguish official NCAA charges from informal gate conventions — such as the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip — which are not part of the published schedule and should not be confused with mandatory fees. Vehicle restrictions apply within the crater and conservation area, governing which vehicles may descend, permitted hours, and associated vehicle fees that sit alongside entry and conservation charges in the tariff PDF. These three facets together define what every non-East African visitor must comply with versus what is discretionary or operator-driven.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/game-drives/ngorongoro-crater.md:3:The Ngorongoro Crater is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the most concentrated wildlife-viewing areas in Africa. A typical crater game drive starts early from a nearby lodge or campsite (often on the rim), with your driver-guide navigating the steep descent road into the caldera floor. Inside, you can expect to see the Big Five — lion, leopard, elephant, buffalo, and the critically endangered black rhino — often within a single morning. Your driver-guide (such as Emmanuel, cited in Vasilis's trip logs as \"really knowledgeable\") handles vehicle positioning, animal-spotting, and commentary. The day typically includes a picnic lunch at a designated spot on the crater floor (hippos may wander nearby), then an afternoon climb back to the rim. Unscheduled stops are common: Emmanuel facilitated a crater-rim stop where Vasilis bought two Maasai beaded bracelets for ~$20–25 USD (~35,000 TZS). Note that a separate ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash is expected at the Ngorongoro gate — an unwritten convention distinct from the park entry fee and safari cost. Confirm this with your office contact (Richard) before final payment.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/cash-conventions/village-market-stops.md:3:Emmanuel also facilitated a stop at the crater rim where Vasilis bought two Maasai beaded bracelets for Athina Mari, ~$20–25 USD / ~35,000 TZS (source: specialistFacts voice memo)\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/ngorongoro-advisor/knowledge/ngorongoro/tariffs/entry-permits.md:9:These fees are payable in USD for non-East African visitors, reflecting the expectation of foreign currency payment at the gate. The entry permit is completely separate from safari company costs (vehicle hire, guide, accommodation) and informal tips such as the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip sometimes requested at the crater gate.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/database/notes.json:3:  \"description\": \"Personal notes and trip memories — the Stone Town Zanzibar courtyard, Ngorongoro voice-memo facts about Emmanuel and the Maasai bracelets, and the open action item to ask Richard about the ranger tip.\",\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/office-contact.md:7:- **Pre-trip questions**: serving as the go-to person for logistical clarifications before you meet your guide — including any unwritten cash conventions like ranger tips (ask Richard about the ~5,000 TZS Ngorongoro ranger tip before paying the balance, to avoid surprises).\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/index.md:6:Safari logistics in northern Tanzania split between two distinct roles. The office contact (like Richard) handles commercial coordination: booking confirmations, balance payments, and pre-trip communication. The driver-guide (like Emmanuel) is the field expert — a knowledgeable professional who runs the actual game drives, navigates the parks, and provides on-the-ground interpretation. These roles are separate people with different responsibilities, and understanding this split helps avoid confusion about who to ask for what.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/driver-guide.md:3:The driver-guide is your on-the-ground expert throughout the safari. In Vasilis's arrangement, Emmanuel fills this role, and he is described as 'really knowledgeable.' Key responsibilities include:\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/driver-guide.md:6:- **Park navigation**: handling park entries, gate procedures, and inside-the-park logistics — including knowing unwritten conventions like the ~5,000 TZS ranger tip sometimes expected at Ngorongoro gate.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/roles/driver-guide.md:7:- **Cultural facilitation**: Emmanuel also facilitated a stop at the Ngorongoro crater rim where Vasilis bought Maasai beaded bracelets (~$20–25 USD / ~35,000 TZS), showing how driver-guides often connect travelers with local vendors.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/cash-conventions/index.md:6:Northern Tanzania safaris involve unwritten cash conventions that go beyond quoted safari costs. Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash expected at the Ngorongoro gate, separate from park fees — this is an unwritten convention (source: specialistFacts voice memo) Action item: ask Richard about the ranger tip before paying the safari balance, to avoid surprises (source: specialistFacts voice memo) Emmanuel also facilitated a stop at the crater rim where Vasilis bought two Maasai beaded bracelets for Athina Mari, ~$20–25 USD / ~35,000 TZS (source: specialistFacts voice memo) Understanding these before final safari payment avoids surprises.\nsdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/spaces/tanzania-safari-advisor/knowledge/safari/cash-conventions/ranger-tips.md:3:Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS cash expected at the Ngorongoro gate, separate from park fees — this is an unwritten convention (source: specialistFacts voice memo)","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
