{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_yFRfVkQIpmPRuAIEhwm7H52a","type":"tool_result","content":"sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/sessions/e900c068-b4df-4e09-81e0-fc6518470e25/trace.json 87\nHere is a structured summary of all three files:\n\n---\n\n## (1) tanzaniamemories.md — Notes File: Distinct Topics & Facts\n\n**Trip Overview**\n- Travelers: Vasilis + Athina Mari\n- Dates: Aug 3–20, 2026\n- Route: Cairo → Arusha → Safari (Tarangire / Lake Manyara / Ngorongoro) → Arusha → Zanzibar → Dar es Salaam → Cairo → Athens\n- Total flights cost: ~€2,707 (6 legs, both travelers)\n\n**Flight Itinerary** (all confirmed)\n- Aug 3: ATH→CAI, Aegean A3932, 06:55–08:50 (ref ZZJQUU)\n- Aug 4: CAI→DAR, EgyptAir, 22:40–04:20+1\n- Aug 5: DAR→ARK, Precision Air TC144, 10:50–12:00\n- Aug 11: ARK→ZNZ, Precision Air TC145, 12:40–13:40\n- Aug 19: DAR→CAI, EgyptAir, 05:20–11:05\n- Aug 20: CAI→ATH, Aegean A3935, 19:55–22:00 (ref ZZL22S)\n\n**Accommodations** (all confirmed)\n- Eileen Hotel, Cairo — Aug 3–5\n- Serengeti Villa, Arusha — Aug 5–7 (phone +255 757 757 928)\n- Safari lodging (Aug 7–9): Twiga Camp Site (Tarangire, full board) → Twiga Camp Site (Lake Manyara, full board) → Jevas Hotel (Ngorongoro, half board)\n- Kutoka Lodge, Arusha — Aug 9–11\n- Treasures of Zanzibar House — Aug 11–13\n- Ayla Beach House, Zanzibar (Kiwengwa) — Aug 13–17\n- Sunny Shore B&B, Dar es Salaam — Aug 17–19\n- Ramses Hilton, Cairo — Aug 19–20\n\n**Safari Details**\n- Operator: Suricata Safaris Ltd — contact Richard (+255 763 222 293, info@suricatasafaris.com)\n- 3-day group camping safari, Aug 7–9\n- Cost: $1,200 total; $240 deposit paid (20%); $960 balance due on arrival\n- Payment: cash (USD, post-2009 notes) or online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge)\n\n**Key Reservations**\n- The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15, 18:00–20:00, 2 adults, fully paid $46, outdoor seating requested\n\n**Visa & Insurance Requirements**\n- Tanzania e-visa mandatory ($50/person) at visa.immigration.go.tz — visa-on-arrival no longer available as of Jan 2025\n- Egypt e-visa multiple-entry ($65/person) — printed copy mandatory\n- Zanzibar mandatory travel insurance from Zanzibar Insurance Corporation\n\n**Transport & Driving**\n- Zanzibar: International Driving Permit held; local Zanzibar Driving Permit also required (~$15, valid up to 3 months). Police checkpoints frequent; carry both permits.\n- Precision Air flights TC144/TC145 have luggage restrictions favoring soft bags.\n\n**Sightseeing Plans**\n- Cairo Stopover 1 (Aug 3–4): Grand Egyptian Museum, Pyramids of Giza\n- Cairo Stopover 2 (Aug 19–20): Islamic Cairo, Citadel, Khan el-Khalili, Coptic Cairo\n- Dar es Salaam: Kivukoni Fish Market, Kariakoo Market, National Museum, Coco Beach, Bongoyo Island\n\n**Practical Advice**\n- Ngorongoro nights are cold — pack warm layers\n- Zanzibar swimming: north coast (Nungwi) best for consistent conditions\n- August is peak safari season (Great Wildebeest Migration)\n- Safari clothing: Decathlon Forclaz line; DEET insect repellent essential\n- Vasilis prefers bullet lists; communicates in Greek or English\n\n---\n\n## (2) trip-costs.xlsx — Cost Breakdown (from spreadsheet)\n\n| Category | Item | Amount |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Flights** | ATH-CAI-DAR-ARK-ZNZ-DAR-CAI-ATH (6 legs, 2 travelers) | €2,707 |\n| **Safari** | Suricata Safaris 3-day package, 2 pax | $1,200 |\n| | – deposit paid (20%) | $240 |\n| | – balance due on arrival (cash, USD) | $960 |\n| **Park Fees** | Ngorongoro entry permit (2 pax × $70.80) | $141.60 |\n| | Ngorongoro crater service fee (2 pax × $70.80) | $141.60 |\n| | Ngorongoro crater vehicle descent fee (per vehicle/trip, non-EA) | $295.00 |\n| | Tarangire NP entrance (2 pax × $59, peak season) | $118.00 |\n| | Lake Manyara NP entrance (2 pax × $59, peak season) | $118.00 |\n| **Visas** | Tanzania e-visa (2 × $50) | $100.00 |\n| | Egypt e-visa (2 × $65) | $130.00 |\n| **Insurance** | Zanzibar mandatory travel insurance, ZIC (2 × $44) | $88.00 |\n| **Dining** | The Rock Restaurant (paid) | $46.00 |\n| **Transport** | Zanzibar local driving permit (per driver) | $15.00 |\n| **Lodging** | All lodging (excl. safari package) | $951.00 |\n| **TOTAL (USD)** | (excl. EUR flights) | **$3,344.20** |\n\n---\n\n## (3) ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf — Every Fee, Category & Condition\n\n### A. ENTRY PERMIT (per person, valid 24 hours single entry)\n\n| Age Group | Non-East African (USD) | East African (TZS) | Expatriates/Residents (USD) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 16 years and above | $70.80 | TZS 11,800 | $35.40 |\n| 5 to 16 years | $23.60 | TZS 2,360 | $11.80 |\n| Below 5 years | Free | Free | Free |\n\n**Crew fee** (Tanzanian safari crew with valid IDs): TZS 1,770 per person/day\n\n### B. MOTOR VEHICLE PERMIT (per vehicle, private vehicle rates shown)\n\n| Tare Weight | Private Vehicle (TZS) | Commercial Vehicle (TZS) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Up to 2,000 kg | TZS 236,000 | TZS 118,000 |\n| 2,001–3,000 kg | TZS 295,000 | TZS 177,000 |\n| 3,001–7,000 kg | TZS 354,000 | N/A |\n| 7,001 kg and above | TZS 413,000 | N/A |\n\n### C. ENTRY TO CULTURAL BOMAS — $20.00 per vehicle (USD)\n\n### D. CAMPING FEES (per person per day)\n\n| Age Group | Non-East African (USD) | Tanzanian (TZS) | East African (TZS) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 16 years and above | $47.20 | TZS 11,800 | TZS 11,800 |\n| 5 to 16 years | $11.80 | TZS 5,900 | TZS 5,900 |\n| Below 5 years | Free | Free | Free |\n| Safari crew (Tanzanian) | TZS 2,300 (TZS) | — | — |\n\n### E. CRATER SERVICE FEE (per person)\n\n| Age Group | Non-East African (USD) | Tanzanian (TZS) | East African (TZS) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 16 years and above | $70.80 | TZS 17,700 | TZS 17,000 |\n| 5 to 16 years | $35.40 | TZS 8,850 | TZS 8,850 |\n| Below 5 years | Free | Free | Free |\n| Safari crew (Tanzanian) | TZS 4,720 (TZS) | — | — |\n\n**Vehicle descent fee (Crater floor):**\n- Non-East African: **$295.00 per vehicle/trip**\n- Tanzanian & East African citizens: N/A (included)\n- Only 4×4 vehicles up to 3,500 kg tare weight allowed on Crater floor.\n\n**1. Public Campsite** — same rates as Crater Service Fee\n**2. Special Campsite** — rates on application (must be reserved in advance)\n\n### F. WALKING SAFARI GUIDE FEES\n\n| Category | Tanzanian (TZS) | Non-EA (USD) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Short walks (1–4 hrs), adults | TZS 11,800 | $23.60 |\n| Short walks, children (12–16 yrs) | TZS 5,900 | $11.80 |\n| Long walks (above 4 hrs), adults | TZS 23,600 | $29.50 |\n| Long walks, children | TZS 11,800 | $17.70 |\n| Endoro Nature Trail & Elephant Caves, adult | TZS 11,800 | $17.70 |\n| Endoro Nature Trail & Elephant Caves, child | TZS 5,900 | $11.80 |\n\n### G. PERMIT FEE FOR SERVING HOT LUNCH (Bush Lunch) — $11.80 per person, Non-EA; TZS 5,900 per Tanzanian\n\n### H. LANDING FEES FOR AIRCRAFT\n\n| Aircraft Category | Local Registered (TZS) | Foreign Registered (USD) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Up to 4 Seater — Private | TZS 11,800 | $59.00 |\n| Up to 4 Seater — Commercial | TZS 17,700 | $141.60 |\n| 5–12 Seater — Private | TZS 17,700 | $141.60 |\n| 5–12 Seater — Commercial | TZS 23,600 | $200.60 |\n| 13–20 Seater — Private | TZS 23,600 | $200.60 |\n| 13–20 Seater — Commercial | TZS 41,300 | $377.60 |\n| Over 20 Seater — Private | TZS 59,000 | N/A |\n| Over 20 Seater — Commercial | TZS 70,800 | N/A |\n\n### I. OLDUVAI GORGE / SHIFTING SAND / LAETOLI FOOTPRINTS\n\n| Age Group | East African (TZS) | Non-East African (USD) |\n|---|---|---|\n| 16 years and above | TZS 35,400 | $35.40 |\n| 5 to 16 years | TZS 11,800 | $11.80 |\n| Below 5 years | Free | Free |\n\n### J. HOT AIR BALLOON SAFARIS\n\n| Age Group | East African (TZS) | Non-East African (USD) |\n|---|---|---|\n| 8 years and above | TZS 47,200 | $39.53 |\n| Below 8 years | TZS 11,800 | N/A |\n\n### K. HORSE RIDING SAFARIS (per person)\n\n| Age Group | East African (TZS) | Non-East African (USD) |\n|---|---|---|\n| 16 years and above | TZS 11,800 | $17.70 |\n| Below 16 years