{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_xkFx1liGW8ZrU0D9JMmm1SQn","type":"tool_result","content":"SEQ 87 delegate_4_d26efc8f\nHere is a structured summary of all three files:\n\n---\n\n## (1) tanzaniamemories.md — Notes File: Distinct Topics & Facts\n\n**Trip Overview**\n- Travelers: Vasilis + Athina Mari\n- Dates: Aug 3–20, 2026\n- Route: Cairo → Arusha → Safari (Tarangire / Lake Manyara / Ngorongoro) → Arusha → Zanzibar → Dar es Salaam → Cairo → Athens\n- Total flights cost: ~€2,707 (6 legs, both travelers)\n\n**Flight Itinerary** (all confirmed)\n- Aug 3: ATH→CAI, Aegean A3932, 06:55–08:50 (ref ZZJQUU)\n- Aug 4: CAI→DAR, EgyptAir, 22:40–04:20+1\n- Aug 5: DAR→ARK, Precision Air TC144, 10:50–12:00\n- Aug 11: ARK→ZNZ, Precision Air TC145, 12:40–13:40\n- Aug 19: DAR→CAI, EgyptAir, 05:20–11:05\n- Aug 20: CAI→ATH, Aegean A3935, 19:55–22:00 (ref ZZL22S)\n\n**Accommodations** (all confirmed)\n- Eileen Hotel, Cairo — Aug 3–5\n- Serengeti Villa, Arusha — Aug 5–7 (phone +255 757 757 928)\n- Safari lodging (Aug 7–9): Twiga Camp Site (Tarangire, full board) → Twiga Camp Site (Lake Manyara, full board) → Jevas Hotel (Ngorongoro, half board)\n- Kutoka Lodge, Arusha — Aug 9–11\n- Treasures of Zanzibar House — Aug 11–13\n- Ayla Beach House, Zanzibar (Kiwengwa) — Aug 13–17\n- Sunny Shore B&B, Dar es Salaam — Aug 17–19\n- Ramses Hilton, Cairo — Aug 19–20\n\n**Safari Details**\n- Operator: Suricata Safaris Ltd — contact Richard (+255 763 222 293, info@suricatasafaris.com)\n- 3-day group camping safari, Aug 7–9\n- Cost: $1,200 total; $240 deposit paid (20%); $960 balance due on arrival\n- Payment: cash (USD, post-2009 notes) or online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge)\n\n**Key Reservations**\n- The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar — Aug 15, 18:00–20:00, 2 adults, fully paid $46, outdoor seating requested\n\n**Visa & Insurance Requirements**\n- Tanzania e-visa mandatory ($50/person) at visa.immigration.go.tz — visa-on-arrival no longer available as of Jan 2025\n- Egypt e-visa multiple-entry ($65/person) — printed copy mandatory\n- Zanzibar mandatory travel insurance from Zanzibar Insurance Corporation\n\n**Transport & Driving**\n- Zanzibar: International Driving Permit held; local Zanzibar Driving Permit also required (~$15, valid up to 3 months). Police checkpoints frequent; carry both permits.\n- Precision Air flights TC144/TC145 have luggage restrictions favoring soft bags.\n\n**Sightseeing Plans**\n- Cairo Stopover 1 (Aug 3–4): Grand Egyptian Museum, Pyramids of Giza\n- Cairo Stopover 2 (Aug 19–20): Islamic Cairo, Citadel, Khan el-Khalili, Coptic Cairo\n- Dar es Salaam: Kivukoni Fish Market, Kariakoo Market, National Museum, Coco Beach, Bongoyo Island\n\n**Practical Advice**\n- Ngorongoro nights are cold — pack warm layers\n- Zanzibar swimming: north coast (Nungwi) best for consistent conditions\n- August is peak safari season (Great Wildebeest Migration)\n- Safari clothing: Decathlon Forclaz line; DEET insect repellent essential\n- Vasilis prefers bullet lists; communicates in Greek or English\n\n---\n\n## (2) trip-costs.xlsx — Cost Breakdown (from spreadsheet)\n\n| Category | Item | Amount |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Flights** | ATH-CAI-DAR-ARK-ZNZ-DAR-CAI-ATH (6 legs, 2 travelers) | €2,707 |\n| **Safari** | Suricata Safaris 3-day package, 2 pax | $1,200 |\n| | – deposit paid (20%) | $240 |\n| | – balance due on arrival (cash, USD) | $960 |\n| **Park Fees** | Ngorongoro entry permit (2 pax × $70.80) | $141.60 |\n| | Ngorongoro crater service fee (2 pax × $70.80) | $141.60 |\n| | Ngorongoro crater vehicle descent fee (per vehicle/trip, non-EA) | $295.00 |\n| | Tarangire NP entrance (2 pax × $59, peak season) | $118.00 |\n| | Lake Manyara NP entrance (2 pax × $59, peak season) | $118.00 |\n| **Visas** | Tanzania e-visa (2 × $50) | $100.00 |\n| | Egypt e-visa (2 × $65) | $130.00 |\n| **Insurance** | Zanzibar mandatory travel insurance, ZIC (2 × $44) | $88.00 |\n| **Dining** | The Rock Restaurant (paid) | $46.00 |\n| **Transport**